               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360201-name-1159" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360201-name-1159" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360201-name-1159" type="surname" value="BRAND"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360201-name-1159" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM BRAND</persName>
                  </hi>. I was groom to Mr. Edward Laforest, a wine<lb></lb>merchant</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183602010203"></xptr>
               <p>in John-street, Bedford-row, and lived in the stable. I have known the prisoner a great many years—on the 3rd of January, I had occasion to go to Hammersmith for my master, and met the prisoner at the West-end—he said he was out of service, and asked if I could tell him of a place—he went with me to Hammersmith, and at last I invited him home, and we had some refreshment—he staid with me a quarter of an hour—soon after he was gone I missed an Indian-rubber cloak of my master's from the harness-room—my room adjoins that—I saw him the next day in Union-street, Whitechapel—when he saw me, he ran away—I called "Stop thief", and overtook him in the Commercial-road—I found the cloak on his back, and gave him into custody—this is it.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner put in a written defence stating that the prosecutor had made him intoxicated, and he was unconscious of having the cloak till the next morning.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360201-name-1160" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360201-name-1160" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360201-name-1160" type="surname" value="BRAND"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360201-name-1160" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM BRAND</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi>. I did not lend him the cloak—there is not a word of truth in that—he did not tell me he was going to take it—he was not drunk—we had some half-and-half and biscuits, but nothing else.</p>
